Remarks . The general appearance of the species superficially resembles members of
Heteropilumnus De Man, 1895
, and its allies (
Ser Rathbun, 1931
;
Zehntneriana Ng & Takeda, 2010
), except that it lacks the long setae that lines the margins of the carapace, chelipeds and ambulatory legs and/or the dense velvet-like tomentum that covers the carapace (cf. Ng 1989 ; Ng & Davie 1991 ; Ng & Lin 2015 ; Ng & Tan 1988 ;
Ng et al. 2018
;
Lee et al. 2015
).
